<form name=ncl1 method=post action="#">
<fieldset>
<legend>List of documents to be attached
</legend>

	<label style="width:900px;">1. Identity Proof- Voter ID Card/ Passport/Driver’s License/RSBY Card/Aadhaar Card/ Identity card issued by Govt. or Semi Govt. organisations/PAN Card/ MNREGA Job Card</label>  
	<label style="width:900px;">2. Address proof-  Voter ID Card/ Passport/Driver’s License/ Aadhaar Card/ Electricity Bill/ Water Bill/ Extracts of 7/12 and 8 A / Rent Receipt/Telephone Bill/ Ration Card/Property Tax Receipt</label> 
<label style="width:900px;">3. Proof of caste for self– School leaving certificate mentioning caste / Bonafide certificate (mentioning caste) issued by school / self attested Xerox of caste certificate / If uneducated birth registration extract / Caste and residence certificate issued by Sarpanch/Local Police/Corporator</label> 
<label style="width:900px;">4. Affidavit for caste</label>
<label style="width:900px;">5. Income proof – Income tax return for previous 3 financial years, if applicant is salaried or self employed or businessman / Income certificate from Tahsildar for 3 years, if applicant is farmer or labourer / Affidavit mentioning income for last 3 years</label><br>
<hr color="ffff">
	<legend>Additional Documents to be produced as applicable</legend><br>
<label style="width:900px;">1. Property tax receipt</label>
<label style="width:900px;">2. If proof of father’s caste not available, a relative’s caste certificate and  genealogical affidavit with details of relation to relative</label>
<label style="width:900px;">3. If applicant migrated from other state/ district, then caste certificate of applicant’s father  issued by competent authority in that state/district</label>
<label style="width:900px;">4. If married women,<br>a. Proof of caste before marriage, as prescribed in point no. 3<br>
	b. Proof of marriage- marriage registration certificate and name change notification in gazette</label>  
<label style="width:900px;">5. If applicant is Muslim (either of the following document may be submitted)<br>
	a) A Investigation report of Tahsildar if his/her father’s caste certificate is not available<br>
	b) Caste certificate issued by registered Muslim Societies</label>
<label style="width:900px;">6. Proof of caste of a relative- Father/Brother/Sister/Grandfather/Uncle/Aunt or any other blood relation-<br>
	 a. School leaving certificate<br>
	 b. Birth/death extract<br>
	 c. If in Government service, extract of first page of service book<br>
	 d. Document certifying caste issued by department of social justice</label> 	
</fieldset>
